# Swift iOS Rules (ResumeBuilder)

## Signing and TestFlight

- Verify signing, bundle ID, archive status, privacy strings before any TestFlight claim.
- Dark mode only: do not change `.preferredColorScheme(.dark)`.

## SwiftUI Navigation

- Create a tracked spec artifact before changing SwiftUI navigation or app structure.
- `navigationDestination` goes on ZStack/ScrollView inside NavigationStack, never on List or nested subviews.

## Architecture

- Extend `Features/V2/` folder, not the older `Features/` folder.
- Use `@Observable` + `@MainActor`, not `ObservableObject`/`@Published`.
- Swift 6 strict concurrency: every new type must be `Sendable` or `@MainActor`.
- No hardcoded API URLs; use the `Endpoint` enum via `APIClient`.
- `API_BASE_URL` comes from Info.plist, not from source code.

## Self-Learning

After any mistake, correction, failed build, or bad pattern: add a lesson to `tasks/lessons.md` immediately.

## Progress Updates

After any meaningful task or story completion: update `tasks/progress.md`.
